translations.5630690605964735914: The most important options here are {$START_TAG_STRONG}Fixed plus dynamic{$CLOSE_TAG_STRONG} and {$START_TAG_SPAN}Dynamic but at least fixed{$CLOSE_TAG_SPAN}{$LINE_BREAK} If the {$START_TAG_SPAN}Fixed plus dynamic{$CLOSE_TAG_SPAN} price model is used the service price will be the sum of fixed price and dynamic price.{$LINE_BREAK} If the {$START_TAG_SPAN}Dynamic but at least fixed{$CLOSE_TAG_SPAN} price model is used the service price will be the fixed price if the fixed price is greater than dynamic price or dynamic price if dynamic price is greater than the fixed price.

translations.5903926530016896022: Start date and end date are useful when you want to change pricing. If you're not making any pricing change, just leave the fields empty. To change pricing, set an end date for the old rule and a start date for the new pricing rule. When start date is empty the rule applies "since the beginning of time" and when the end date is empty the rule applies "until the end of time". A [start date - end date] time interval includes the full start date and the full end date.
